method for c...","Define organizational structure, bands, and grades structures","Identify the signs that your company needs effective human resource systems and processes","Outline the seven essential human resource systems and processes","Describe a step by step method for creating an organizational structure","Discuss how to set up the band and grade structure","Explain why you need an efficient human resource process in your company"],"courseDescription":"<p>Bands or Grades form part of methods to decide the seniority and expectations for a specific role. This free online course introduces you to grade and band structures and why they are necessary for a company. Discover a step-by-step method of setting up a grade and band structure. You will familiarize yourself with the various signs which tell you that your company needs effective human resource systems and processes. You will learn the seven essential human resource systems and processes that you must have in your company.</p><p>Having an organizational structure in place allows companies to remain efficient and focused. After subsequent sections of the course, you will better understand the organizational structure and see why it is essential for companies. You will also learn a step-by-step method to set up an organizational structure for your own company. Find out why human resource policies are vital in an organization, the twelve essential policies, and examine how to modify these policies to suit your organizational needs.</p><p>Having a solid band or grade structure will help highlight employees being under-compensated or over-compensated in their roles. Further on in the course, you will see examples of band structures and how they influence strategic compensation decisions. This course is beneficial to owners of small and medium enterprises, and human resource professionals who want to broaden their knowledge of all aspects of the human resource domain. Sign up for this course and start learning to